Init_CLISELF_CLISubroutine

Initialize an instance of the CLI class using a provided configuration file An example configuration file can be found in self/etc/config_example.json The initialization procedure initilizes a json_file class (from json-fortran) and a COMMAND_LINE_INTERFACE class (from FLAP). Further, the CLI options are set according to the self_model.options field in the configuration file.

Init_LagrangeSELF_LagrangeSubroutine

Initialize an instance of the Lagrange class On output, all of the attributes for the Lagrange class are allocated and values are initialized according to the number of control points, number of target points, and the types for the control and target nodes. If a GPU is available, device pointers for the Lagrange attributes are allocated and initialized.

Graph Key

Nodes of different colours represent the following:

Solid arrows point from a procedure to one which it calls. Dashed arrows point from an interface to procedures which implement that interface. This could include the module procedures in a generic interface or the implementation in a submodule of an interface in a parent module. Where possible, edges connecting nodes are given different colours to make them easier to distinguish in large graphs.
